on></figure><p><b>Ba Ho Waterfalls</b> — about <b>25 km north, ~40 minutes</b> by scooter. Three cascades, swimming, trekking, cliff jumps. A perfect 50cc target: close, beautiful, refreshing in the heat. Hon Chong is easy to add on the way.</p><h2>A full day — mind your 50cc</h2><figure><img src="img/article/marshr-doroga.jpg" alt="Out of town — highway and green fields on the way to the beaches" loading="lazy"><figcaption>Out of town — highway and green fields on the way to the beaches</figcaption></figure><p><b>Doc Let Beach</b> — about <b>50 km north</b>, white sand and calm sea. On a 50cc that&rsquo;s a full day along the QL1A highway: plan your time, fuel and leave early. If you want long trips often, a bigger bike helps — but for a relaxed day, Doc Let on a 50cc is doable.</p><h2>Tips for 50cc trips</h2><ul><li>Fuel up in advance — <b>RON 95</b>; stations are rarer out of town.</li><li><b>Helmet + papers</b> always: see <a href="shtrafy-2026-en.html">fines 2026</a> and <a href="policiya-baik-en.html">what to do if police stop you</a>.</li><li>Leave in the morning — cooler and less traffic.</li><li>In the rainy season check the forecast: mountain roads wash out.</li><li>Look after the bike in the heat — <a href="uhod-za-baikom-en.html">scooter care</a>.</li></ul><h2>A bike for all these trips</h2><p>If you plan several rides, <a href="arenda-vs-pokupka-en.html">buying with a 50% buy-back</a> usually beats renting: ride as much as you like, then get half the price back before you leave. Our bikes are <b>50cc, no licence</b>, with clean papers and a warranty.</p><p style="margin-top:24px"><a href="catalog-en.html" class="btn btn-wa">See bikes &rarr;</a> <a href="arenda-vs-pokupka-en.html" class="btn btn-tg" style="margin-left:8px">Rent or buy &rarr;</a></p></div></section><footer><div class="wrap"><div class="fgrid"><div><h4>50cc bikes in Nha Trang</h4><p>Affordable, turnkey 50cc bikes — serviced, washed, with papers. No licence needed: land, buy, ride.</p><div 